          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\nReport: `docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\nFinding: #23\n\nMoved from mistakenly filed meta issue: ConcaveTrillion/ocr-container-meta#316\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `pyproject.toml:43`\n- `pyproject.toml:85`\n\n`python-doctr` is redirected to a Git URL without explicit revision in `pyproject.toml`. The lock pins a commit today, but `uv lock --upgrade` can move it to arbitrary upstream code.\n\nImpact:\n\n- Dependency upgrades can pull unreviewed source outside normal release-version review.\n\nRemediation:\n\n- Use a released `python-doctr` version if possible.\n- Otherwise pin the Git source to an immutable tag/commit in `pyproject.toml` and document upgrade procedure.\n\n---\nThis issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-25T02:48:49Z",
          "comments": {
            "nodes": [
              {
                "author": {
                  "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
                },
                "body": "Fixed in commit 81a0a22: pinned python-doctr git source to SHA 390330ebe4fe25f214d84df89dc0f9b4dcdbf447 in [tool.uv.sources].",
