          "author_association": "OWNER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\n    Report: `pd-book-tools/docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\n    Finding: #23\n\n    ## Summary\n\n    python-doctr is redirected to a Git URL without explicit revision in pyproject.toml.\n\n    ## Impact\n\n    uv lock --upgrade can pull unreviewed upstream source outside normal release-version policy.\n\n    ## Evidence\n\n    - `pyproject.toml:43`\n- `pyproject.toml:85`\n\n    ## Acceptance\n\n    - [ ] Use a released python-doctr version if possible.\n- [ ] Otherwise pin the Git source to an immutable tag/commit and document upgrades.\n\n    ## Notes\n\n    This issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
